column15:
Added these talking points as well: 

The timing is critical to utilize generous, stackable, federal grants from EPA Clean School Bus Program and Direct Pay credits from the Inflation Reduction Act (30% rebates for buses, charging infrastructure, and more) through 2032! Additionally, sales tax for EV school buses are waived in WA and charging infrastructure qualifies for alternative fuel credits!  Plus, this would be a great use of Climate Commitment Act dollars to helps schools access this federal funding. Also consider repowers for cost savings, and partnerships with utilities for community/grid resilience projects!

Funding support:
EPA Clean School Bus Program: https://www.epa.gov/cleanschoolbus
Inflation Reduction Act "Direct Pay" credits: https://home.treasury.gov/news/press-releases/jy2016
Waved sales tax in WA: https://dor.wa.gov/sites/default/files/2022-02/sn_19_ElectricVehicleBuses.pdf 
Alternative Fuel Credits: https://apps.ecology.wa.gov/publications/UIPages/documents/2302087.pdf

Repowers: 
https://www.wri.org/insights/repowering-electric-school-buses

Grid resilience projects: 
https://www.wri.org/insights/electric-school-bus-vehicle-grid-programs 
https://electricschoolbusinitiative.org/all-about-total-cost-ownership-tco-electric-school-buses 
https://www.sdgenews.com/article/sdge-and-cajon-valley-union-school-district-flip-switch-regions-first-vehicle-grid-project
